How to Use & Care\
\'95 Handle your hand-carved wooden keepsake chest gently and wipe it with a soft, dry cloth.\
\'95 Keep the chest away from direct moisture and prolonged sunlight to preserve its carving and natural finish.\
\'95 Dust the brass elephant regularly with a soft, dry cloth and polish occasionally using a suitable brass cleaner to maintain its natural lustre.\
\'95 Handle the blue pottery bowls with care and clean them gently using a soft cloth. Avoid sudden temperature changes and harsh abrasives.\
\'95 The Ajrakh stole is best gently hand-washed in cold water or dry-cleaned to protect its natural dyes.\
\'95 Cared for thoughtfully, your keepsake collection will continue to celebrate Indian craftsmanship and become a treasured heirloom for years to come.\
